Synopsis:
   $uh(<nick> ...)

Description:
   This function is just like the builtin userhost(6) except that it
   queries the server instead of trying to grab the userhost from cache.

Returns:
   Returns the userhost (user@hostname) of each nick passed to it,
   or <UNKNOWN>@<UNKNOWN> if the nick is not online.

History:
   This function first appeared in the "guh" script that is distributed
   with EPIC. It was written by Jeremy Nelson <jnelson@epicsol.org>.

See Also:
   userhost(6)

